narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Somehow, the merits of the language managed to shine through despite the class itself, so if you can take it with Marta, do it.
Absolutely not. One of the worst classes of my life. Jackson is horrendously bad
Yes, I would definitely recommend it. It's a fun, chill course, and totally worth your while if you want to learn Brazilian portuguese :)
It truly depends on the professor. I've heard Marta's better, but Prof. Jackson is such a sweet guy (and really smart). Portuguese is also awesome, so learn it.

Portuguese 120 will really help any student to learn portuguese. After taking this class you will know a lot of information about Brazil and the Brazilian culture, and you will also have been exposed to all the grammar forms which make up the Brazilian Portuguese language. I would definitely recommend taking this class, but would warn that a student must practice the language often outside of class in order to get the full benefit of the course.
